I think it's best to just early exit if we see that there's corruption, instead of calling backupRecord again. I know it's safe to keep calling backupRecord, but generally when we see that the current state isn't what we expect it's best to just bail. So I'd rewrite this as:
for (ConsumerRecord<byte[], []> r : iterable) {
    backupRecord(r);
    if (commandTopicBackup.commandTopicCorruption()) {
        return records;
    }
    records.add(record);
}
return records;

